parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to stall, jerk, or hesitate, leading to loss of control, accidents, or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission hesitates or jerks when shifting
or fails to shift into gear. The vehicle may stall
or lurch forward. The transmission may rev high and not shift back down when the gas pedal is pressed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the clutch hydraulic system can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission "shift shock" problem can cause the vehicle to jerk or hesitate when shifting, leading to loss of control or accidents.
symptoms: The transmission hesitates or jerks when shifting
particularly in 1st and 2nd gear. The vehicle may experience a hard "thump" when accelerating from a slow speed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A cracked exhaust manifold can cause reduced engine performance, decreased power, and potentially lead to carbon monoxide poisoning due to exhaust fumes entering the passenger compartment.
symptoms: and exhaust fumes entering the passenger compartment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty catalytic converter can cause the vehicle to fail emissions inspections, leading to potential environmental harm and increased emissions.
The check engine light can indicate various engine problems, potentially leading to reduced engine performance, decreased power, and increased emissions.
Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, potentially leading to accidents and injuries.
The failure of the brake caliper can cause a loss of braking performance, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: knocking or grinding noise when applying the brakes

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake master cylinder can cause a complete loss of braking performance, leading to accidents or near-misses.
The failure of the brake pads can cause a loss of braking performance, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: grinding or squealing noise when applying the brakes
